data.title: Across State Lines: Tzionis Makes Debut in Serbia

data.text:
After his transfer from Sporting KC to FK Cukaricki in Serbia, Marinos Tzionis made his debut this past weekend in Serbia. Tzionis was a second half substitute coming off the bench in the 63rd minute in Cukaricki’s 3-1 win over FK Vojvodina. The score when Tzionis entered was already the games final score a 3-1.

Another former Sporting player has a new club as center back, Nicolas Isimat-Mirin has signed on to play in Greece with Greek Super League club Athens Kallithea for their season.

Here’s this week’s full update.

SKC – former Sporting KC players

ACA – former Sporting KC academy players (finished with college eligibility)

KC – Kansas City area players

SPR – former Swope Park Rangers/Sporting KC II players

COL – local college players

Comets – former Comets players

FCKC – former FC Kansas City players
